<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="98" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="98">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="98">
Males and females with swollen fourth femur; H-shaped eye arrangement, recurved PER; high clypeus; tarsal organs pattern (4-4-3-3); legs lacking spines. Male palpal tibia enlarged, papal bulb with conspicuous seminal duct (
<bibRefCitation author="Henrard, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="18" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 104" title="An overview of Afrotropical canopydwelling Orchestina (Araneae, Oonopidae) with a wealth of remarkable sexual dimorphic characters." volume="3281" year="2012">
Henrard and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Jocqué">Jocque</normalizedToken>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Izquierdo, MA" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History" pageId="18" pageNumber="105" pagination="1 - 362" title="Taxonomic revision of the jumping goblin spiders of the genus Orchestina Simon, 1882, in the Americas (Araneae: Oonopidae)." url="https://www.doi.org/10.1206/0003-0090-410.1.1" volume="410" year="2017">
Izquierdo and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ramírez">Ramirez</normalizedToken>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
